Researchers at University of California, Berkeley,
have managed to grow human heart cells on

00:01:41.370 --> 00:01:42.440
a computer chip.

00:01:42.440 --> 00:01:47.260
They’re grown from stem cells and surrounded
by micro fluid channels which supply them

00:01:47.260 --> 00:01:49.049
with nutrients and drugs.

00:01:49.049 --> 00:01:53.370
The heart cells could be modified to model
human genetic diseases and could eliminate

00:01:53.370 --> 00:01:56.119
the need for the animal testing of drugs.

