00:02:38.970 --> 00:02:44.250
Researchers at MIT have developed a new way
to stimulate brain tissue with magnets.

00:02:44.250 --> 00:02:48.821
By injecting magnetic iron oxide particles
into the brain, and then exposing them to

00:02:48.821 --> 00:02:53.560
an alternating magnetic field, the particles
heat up and stimulate their surrounding brain

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:54.560
tissue.

00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:58.420
This new method could revolutionize the way
neurological diseases like parkinson's are

00:02:58.420 --> 00:02:59.420
treated.

00:02:59.420 --> 00:03:04.560
And the procedure is wireless non-invasive,
and could be remote controlled.

